i [
hyperborea
] Recorded from Norway ( Hessle, 1917 ); northern Arctic Seas, Northern Japan , Atlantic Ocean ( Nilsson, 1928 ); Bering Sea, Spitzbergen, Siberia ( Annenkova, 1929 —this record indicates the presence of 2–3 rows of teeth on the uncini which puts this in the genus
